The paper deals with capacity maximization in wireless networks, which is a problem in information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The game theoretic approach used in the paper is a well-known technique in computer science (cs.GT). The paper also discusses distributed algorithms, which fall under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper provides simulation studies, which could be considered as a form of systems and control (cs.SI).
